	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=85751><span id= >Joim</span></a><br><span id=notbold>1 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Sure, warriors can get big crips, but what about paladins with Slay Undead 3?<br>Level 3 Slay Undead allows paladins to get slay hits for over 100 times the base damage of the weapon, allowing a melee hit for almost 8000 with this amazing hammer.<br><br>But yes, this would be the ultimate weapon for an auto-riposte discing warrior/monk; significantly better than a weighted axe:<br>Modal damage for weighted axe at 60 is 110 (from damage bonus) + 2x45 (base damage) = 200<br>Modal damage for Drathor Great Hammer at 60 is 84 (supposing the damage bonus at 60 for 95 delay is 73 as in the screenshot) + 2x74 (base damage) = 232<br>So the modal damage on the hammer is better on ripostes (delay independent), and better per time on auto-attack because of the higher modal damage and also lower delay. (disclaimer: modal damage per delay isn't the only important thing to look at when comparing weapons)<br><br>All in all, I'd love a pair of these hammers - one for both my monk and paladin.<br>- Joim<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Mon Mar 11 19:22:59 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
